.SH COMPATIBILITY
This \fBbeep\fP's argument format is generally compatible with the one commonly
found in Linux, though it lacks the \fB\-s\fP and \fB\-c\fP flags and support for
long options. Snippets written for that \fBbeep\fP usually work with this one, so
long as they only use the short flags.
